# Installation Guide

## Clone Repository

```bash
git clone YOUR_GITHUB_REPOSITORY_LINK
cd amazon-connect-analytics
```

---

## Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

# Docker Deployment

## Start Containers

```bash
docker-compose up --build
```

This initializes:
- Kafka
- Zookeeper
- PostgreSQL
- Dashboard services

---

# Run Kafka Producer

```bash
python kafka/producer.py
```

---

# Run Kafka Consumer

```bash
python etl/consumer.py
```

---

# Launch Dashboard

```bash
streamlit run dashboards/app.py
```

Dashboard URL:

```text
http://localhost:8501
```

---

# Real-Time Processing Workflow

## Step 1
The call data generator continuously creates simulated customer interaction records.

## Step 2
Kafka Producer streams events into the Kafka Broker in real time.

## Step 3
Kafka Consumer processes streaming operational events.

## Step 4
PostgreSQL stores analytics-ready datasets inside the operational warehouse.

## Step 5
The Streamlit dashboard visualizes operational intelligence metrics in real time.

